programme.title: Manchester United vs Ipswich Town (MW27)
programme.desc: Manchester United have lost seven Premier League home games this season, with five of those coming in Ruben Amorim's seven in charge. They last lost more at Old Trafford in a single league campaign back in 1962-63 (9).

programme.title: Tottenham Hotspur vs AFC Bournemouth (MW28)
programme.desc: Only Mohamed Salah (16) has scored more away goals in the Premier League this season than Justin Kluivert (10), with the Dutchman's 10 goals on the road the most ever by a Bournemouth player in a single top-flight campaign.

programme.title: Fulham vs Liverpool (MW31)
programme.desc: Liverpool have scored 38 goals in 15 away Premier League matches this season, an average of 2.53 goals per game. That is their joint best in a top-flight season, also scoring at the same rate in 2013-14 (48 in 19 games, 2.53).

programme.title: Arsenal vs Chelsea (MW29)
programme.desc: Arsenal are unbeaten in their last six Premier League games against Chelsea (W4 D2), their longest run without a league defeat against them since a run of 19 between 1995 and 2005.

programme.title: Liverpool vs Everton (MW30)
programme.desc: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 24 Premier League home games against Everton (W14 D9), winning five of the last six at Anfield.

programme.title: Manchester City vs Crystal Palace (MW32)
programme.desc: Crystal Palace are unbeaten in their last 10 away games in the Premier League (W6 D4); never before in their league history have they had a longer run without defeat on the road.

programme.title: Aston Villa vs Newcastle United (MW33)
programme.desc: Aston Villa have lost five of their last six Premier League games against Newcastle (W1), as many as they had in their previous 16 against the Magpies in the division (W4 D7).

programme.title: Wolverhampton Wanderers vs Tottenham Hotspur (MW32)
programme.desc: Wolves are unbeaten in their last four league games against Tottenham (W3 D1), last having a longer run between May 1968 and February 1970 (5).

programme.title: Brighton and Hove Albion vs West Ham United (MW34)
programme.desc: Brighton have only lost one of their 15 Premier League meetings with West Ham (W6 D8), though it was a 3-1 defeat in this exact fixture last season.

programme.title: Brentford vs Manchester United (MW35)
programme.desc: Brentford have won just one of their last 12 meetings with Manchester United in all competitions (D2 L9), a 4-0 home win in August 2022.

programme.title: Liverpool vs Tottenham Hotspur (MW34)
programme.desc: Liverpool are unbeaten in their last 15 home games against Tottenham in all competitions (W11 D4), winning the last three while scoring four goals each time.

programme.title: Everton vs Southampton (MW37)
programme.desc: This will be Everton's 2,789th and final game at Goodison Park in all competitions (W1537 D660 L591). They're currently winless in seven home games (D5 L2), last having a longer run between October and December 2009 (8).

programme.title: Chelsea vs Liverpool (MW35)
programme.desc: Chelsea are winless in their last 10 meetings with Liverpool in all competitions (D7 L3), only once before going longer without a win over the Reds (11 from 1985 to 1990).

programme.title: Manchester City vs Aston Villa (MW34)
programme.desc: Manchester City have won their last 14 Premier League home games against Aston Villa, scoring at least twice in each of the last 13. Their last defeat was in April 2007 under Stuart Pearce.

programme.title: Arsenal vs Crystal Palace (MW34)
programme.desc: Arsenal have lost just three of their last 36 home Premier League matches (W26 D7), though two of those three have been in London derbies, both defeats to West Ham in December 2023 (0-2) and February this season (0-1).

programme.title: Newcastle United vs Chelsea (MW36)
programme.desc: Chelsea have won 31 Premier League games against Newcastle, only beating Tottenham (37) and West Ham (32) more often in the competition.

programme.title: Liverpool vs Crystal Palace (MW38)
programme.desc: When finishing the season at home, the Premier League champions have won their final match on 13 out of the last 14 occasions. The only exception was Manchester United losing against West Ham in 2006-07.

programme.title: Manchester United vs Aston Villa (MW38)
programme.desc: Manchester United will finish this Premier League campaign without winning two matches in a row all season - it's only the third time in the club's history that they've gone an entire league season without winning back-to-back games.
